{{lang|gv|'''Coonceil ny Gaelgey'''}} ({{lang-en|Manx Gaelic Advisory Council}}<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.minorityrights.org/?lid=5411&tmpl=printpage | title = Manx | publisher = [[Minority Rights Group International]] | accessdate = 9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.unhcr.org/refworld/topic,463af2212,488f25df2,49749c8f5,0,,,.html | format = PDF | title = The Future Development of the Manx Language | publisher = [[Department of Education (Isle of Man)|Isle of Man Department of Education]] |date=December 1995 | accessdate = 9 April 2012}}</ref>) is the regulatory body responsible for the [[Manx language]].
The {{lang|gv|Coonceil}} was set up in December 1985 as a sub-committee of the [[Manx Heritage Foundation]]. It is responsible for the provision of authoritative Manx versions of the titles of government departments and street names, and the creation of new words and phrases.
The {{lang|gv|Coonceil}} supports private, public and voluntary organisations who want to use the language more. Many organisations now make use of the language not only to add value to their services{{Fix|text=how?}} but also to help foster the Island's language and culture.
