'''Jebero''' (Chebero, Xebero, Xihuila) is a moribund Amazonian language spoken by the Jebero people of Peru. It is spoken by only a small number of older adults and belongs to the [[Cahuapanan languages|Cahuapanan family]] together with [[Chayahuita]].

