* {{IPA|/i/}} varies between close front unrounded {{IPAblink|i}}, near-close front unrounded {{IPAblink|i̞}} and close-mid front unrounded {{IPAblink|e}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
* {{IPA|/u/}} varies between near-close near-front rounded {{IPAblink|ʊ}} and close-mid back weakly rounded {{IPAblink|o|o̜}}, with the latter realization being the most usual.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
* {{IPA|/ɘ/}} varies between mid near-front unrounded {{IPAblink|ɛ̝|ɛ̽}} and close-mid central unrounded {{IPAblink|ɘ}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
** {{IPA|/ɘ/}} is shorter than the other vowels, particularly between voiceless consonants.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
** The sequence {{IPA|/ɘn/}} is sometimes realized as a syllabic {{IPA|[n̩]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
* {{IPA|/a/}} varies between open central unrounded {{IPAblink|ä}} and near-open retracted front {{IPAblink|æ|æ̠}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}} The vowel chart in {{Harvcoltxt|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013}} puts {{IPA|/a/}} in the near-open central position {{IPAblink|ɐ}}.
** In closed syllables, {{IPA|/a/}} is realized as open-mid central unrounded {{IPAblink|ɜ}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}

