* {{IPA|/m, p/}} are [[Bilabial consonant|bilabial]], whereas {{IPA|/w/}} is [[Labialized velar consonant|labialized velar]].
* {{IPA|/tʃ/}} is an [[Affricate consonant|affricate]], rather than a plosive.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=98}} It has nevertheless been placed in the table in that manner to save space.
* {{IPA|/n, t, ð, l/}} are [[Laminal consonant|laminal]] [[Denti-alveolar consonant|denti-alveolar]] {{IPA|[{{IPA link|n̪}}, {{IPA link|t̪}}, {{IPA link|ð̞|ð̪}}, {{IPA link|l̪}}]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=100}}
** In the syllable [[Syllable#Coda|coda]], {{IPA|/n/}} is realized with a wider contact, maximally dentoalveolo-velar {{IPA|[n̪͡ŋ]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=100}}
** After {{IPA|/u, a/}}, the denti-alveolar contact is often not made, which makes {{IPA|/n/}} sound more like a velar nasal {{IPAblink|ŋ}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=100}}
** {{IPA|/ð/}} may sometimes sound as if it were a lateral consonant, but it is never realized as lateral.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
* {{IPA|/ɲ, ʎ/}} are dentoalveolo-palatal {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɲ|ɲ̪}}, {{IPA link|ʎ|ʎ̪}}]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=100}}
** {{IPA|/ʎ/}} is sometimes realized as a weak fricative {{IPAblink|ʎ̝|ʎ̪˔}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=101}}
* {{IPA|/h/}} occurs only in the affirmative interjection {{IPA|[ahã]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=98}}
* {{IPA|/r/}} is realized as a [[Flap consonant|flap]] {{IPAblink|ɾ}} in the syllable onset and as a trill {{IPAblink|r}} in the syllable coda.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=100}}
* {{IPA|/ˀr/}} is a glottalized flap {{IPAblink|ɾ|ˀɾ}}. Intervocalically, it is reaized as a sequence {{IPA|[ɾʔ]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Gussenhoven|2013|p=100}}

